{"cells":[{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"# Lesson 1: Import Libraries","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"This notebook explains how to import external libraries into your application. It provides the steps for importing the libraries used throughout the course and offers a high-level overview of how the framework handles imports.","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"### Learning Objectives","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"After completing this lesson, you will be able to import external libraries into your application.","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"### Estimated time ","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"This lab will take approximately **10 minutes** to complete.","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"### Lab Support","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"For support, check out the <a href=\"https://learn.c3.ai/page/help-center\" target=\"_blank\">Help Center</a> for  information.","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"-----","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"## Part 1: Define the imports","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"For this course, we’ll use [`Leaflet`](https://leafletjs.com/reference.html), [`react-leaflet`](https://react-leaflet.js.org/), [`mui`](https://mui.com/material-ui/getting-started/), and [`react-select`](https://react-select.com/home).\n\nSince we’re developing within the C3 ecosystem, we don’t use `npm install` directly. Instead, we define imports in the UI Framework configuration.\n\nThe imports are defined in `academyUI/metadata/ImplLanguage.Runtime` directory. This is where the UI Framework expects your runtime definitions.","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"First, create the **ImplLanguage.Runtime** folder under `academyUI/metadata`.","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"Inside `academyUI/metadata/ImplLanguage.Runtime`, create a new file called\n**js-webpack_c3.json**. The `js-webpack_c3.json` is where you can define the libraries for your application. \n\nThe resulting structure should look like the following:\n\n```\nacademyUI\n├── metadata\n│   ├── ImplLanguage.Runtime\n│   │   └── js-webpack_c3.json\n└── ...\n```\n\n\nCopy and paste following code snippet into `js-webpack_c3.json`.","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":2,"languageId":"json","value":"{\n \"name\": \"js-webpack_c3\",\n \"libraries\": [ \n    \"npm leaflet@1.9.4\",\n    \"npm react-leaflet@4.2.1\",\n    \"npm @mui/material@5.14.0\",\n    \"npm @mui/icons-material@5.14.0\",\n    \"npm react-select@5.4.0\"\n ]\n}","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"-----","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"## Part 2: Resolve the runtime","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"To persist these new node packages in your application, we need to resolve the runtime. \n\n**IMPORTANT:** Before you continue, ensure you run commands against the `academyui` application. You can verify this by selecting **Select Application** in the notebook toolbar, and selecting the application with `root package: academyui`.\n\nRun the following code snippet. This ensures the required npm libraries are available throughout your application.","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":2,"languageId":"javascript","value":"// depending on connection speed, this may take a few minutes\nvar runtime = ImplLanguage.Runtime.forName(\"js-webpack_c3\");\nJs.upsertRuntime(runtime, \"client\");","output":[{"items":[{"mime":"c3/notebook","valu