ge-features\"\n    },\n    \"[typescriptreact]\": {\n        \"editor.defaultFormatter\": \"vscode.typescript-language-features\"\n    }\n}","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"3. Whenever you modify a `.ts` or `.tsx` file, it will automatically format on-save. Here are the default commands to save a file in VS Code:\n    - Mac: `Cmd` + `S`\n    - Linux / Windows: `Ctrl` + `S`","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"-----","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"### Summary\nThis setup lesson defines external libraries in `ImplLanguage.Runtime` and resolves the runtime so Leaflet, React Leaflet, MUI, and React Select are available across the application.","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"<div style=\"display:flex; justify-content:flex-end; margin-top:24px; align-items:center; width:100%;\">\n  <a href=\"./02-render-map.c3nb\"\n     aria-label=\"Go to Lesson 1: Render Map\"\n     style=\"display:inline-flex; align-items:center; justify-content:center; padding:10px 16px; border-radius:10px; text-decoration:none; font-weight:600; border:1px solid #1f6feb; background:#1f6feb; color:#ffffff; box-shadow:0 1px 2px rgba(0,0,0,0.06); transition:transform .15s ease, box-shadow .15s ease;\">\n    Next: Render Map →\n  </a>\n</div>","output":[],"executionSummary":{}}],"metadata":{"id":"47d493d3-c42e-4a0b-b6f9-b0430e406145","serializerVersion":"1","runtime":"js-rhino","appName":"academyui"}}